[
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm seeing a case where a kunit test is failing to compile, but when I copy the contents into the sample, it works fine. I'd like to see the expanded macros to better debug the issue. Is there any way to do that?</p>",
        "id": 469084223,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1725973224
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>in the kunit tests? I don't know, but if you copy it into a sample, then you can use the <code>.rsi</code> target</p>",
        "id": 469104790,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1725977569
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It compiles fine in the sample, though :/</p>",
        "id": 469106444,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1725977914
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This is the error I mentioned:<br>\n<a href=\"https://lore.kernel.org/all/202409112144.dcfxjqII-lkp@intel.com/\">https://lore.kernel.org/all/202409112144.dcfxjqII-lkp@intel.com/</a></p>",
        "id": 469412699,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1726064165
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>seems like a doctest bug, here is a minimal example:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"sd\">/// ```</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// type Y = ();</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// mod m {</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">///     use super::Y;</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">///     fn f() -&gt; Y {}</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// }</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// ```</span>\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">X</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>then:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Text only\"><pre><span></span><code>cargo test\n   Compiling rust v0.0.0 (/tmp/tmp)\n    Finished `test` profile [unoptimized + debuginfo] target(s) in 0.13s\n     Running unittests src/lib.rs (target/debug/deps/rust-48a0867617020c3e)\n\nrunning 0 tests\n\ntest result: ok. 0 passed; 0 failed; 0 ignored; 0 measured; 0 filtered out; finished in 0.00s\n\n   Doc-tests rust\n\nrunning 1 test\ntest src/lib.rs - X (line 1) ... FAILED\n\nfailures:\n\n---- src/lib.rs - X (line 1) stdout ----\nerror[E0432]: unresolved import `super::Y`\n --&gt; src/lib.rs:4:9\n  |\n5 |     use super::Y;\n  |         ^^^^^^^^ no `Y` in the root\n\nerror: aborting due to 1 previous error\n\nFor more information about this error, try `rustc --explain E0432`.\nCouldn't compile the test.\n\nfailures:\n    src/lib.rs - X (line 1)\n\ntest result: FAILED. 0 passed; 1 failed; 0 ignored; 0 measured; 0 filtered out; finished in 0.02s\n\nerror: doctest failed, to rerun pass `--doc`\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 469662954,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1726145095
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>will create an upstream issue</p>",
        "id": 469662986,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1726145102
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>done: <a href=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/130274\">https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/130274</a></p>",
        "id": 469665906,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1726145763
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ohhhhh ... it's because the test is wrapped in <code>fn main</code> so the type declaration is defined inside <code>fn main</code> and not in the top-level module.</p>",
        "id": 469669533,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1726146564
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>guess a simple fix here would be to just wrap the entire test in another <code>mod</code></p>",
        "id": 469679673,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1726148462
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Having a look to some <a href=\"https://github.com/Fabo/linux/commit/5a70950361baaa1422355efc2fcd69d132e25c44#diff-d30ee1ada02db61b66c5e1fe855c79580a5e92a6d5b785d9ce6abedabb0b3313R9\">out of tree Examples</a> it looks like these are disabled due to the issue discussed here. At least enabling them (dropping the <code>ingore</code>) results in </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">E0432</span><span class=\"p\">]:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">unresolved</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"k\">super</span><span class=\"err\">`</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">doctests_kernel_generated</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">3892</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">3892</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">module_platform_driver</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">3893</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">MyRegulatorDriver</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">3894</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"n\">name</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"my_regulator_driver\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">3895</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"n\">license</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"GPL\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">3896</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"o\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">no</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">ModuleType</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">root</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">note</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">this</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">originates</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kr\">macro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"cp\">$crate</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">prelude</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">which</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">comes</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">from</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">expansion</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">of</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kr\">macro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">module_platform_driver</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nightly</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">builds</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">run</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">Z</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kr\">macro</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">backtrace</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">more</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">info</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">CC</span><span class=\"w\">      </span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">doctests_kernel_generated_kunit</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">o</span>\n<span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">E0425</span><span class=\"p\">]:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">cannot</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">find</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">value</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">THIS_MODULE</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"k\">super</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"k\">super</span><span class=\"err\">`</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">doctests_kernel_generated</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">3892</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">3892</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">module_platform_driver</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">3893</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">MyRegulatorDriver</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">3894</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"n\">name</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"my_regulator_driver\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">3895</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"n\">license</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"GPL\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">3896</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"o\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">found</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"k\">super</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"k\">super</span><span class=\"err\">`</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">note</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">this</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">originates</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kr\">macro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"cp\">$crate</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">prelude</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">which</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">comes</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">from</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">expansion</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">of</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kr\">macro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">module_platform_driver</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nightly</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">builds</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">run</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">Z</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kr\">macro</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">backtrace</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">more</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">info</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"546447\">Benno Lossin</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291565-Help/topic/Cargo.20expand.20on.20kunit.20test/near/469679673\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>guess a simple fix here would be to just wrap the entire test in another <code>mod</code></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Yes, exactly <span aria-label=\"grinning\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f600\" role=\"img\" title=\"grinning\">:grinning:</span> Encapsulating the given failing example with something like </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"p\">#</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mod</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nn\">xxx</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"o\">..</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n<span class=\"p\">#</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>makes the compiler happy.</p>\n<p>A nice summary (linked via links found in above issue link <span aria-label=\"wink\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f609\" role=\"img\" title=\"wink\">:wink:</span> ) is <a href=\"https://elastio.github.io/bon/blog/the-weird-of-function-local-types-in-rust\">The weird of function-local types in Rust</a>.</p>\n<p>Btw, reading that, especially the part of the Summary \"<em>if you need to add <code>use super::*</code> in your macro-generated code, then this is already a bad call</em>\" makes me wonder if we have to re-think the <code>super</code> usage in <a href=\"https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/torvalds/linux.git/tree/rust/macros/module.rs#n232\">module_init()</a> (compare the errors given above)?</p>",
